    <item>
      <title>Re: Shop module required?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/bcsimplesubscription/forum/general/shop_module_required/re_shop_module_required</link>
      <description>Hello Espen R,&#13;
	&#13;
Apologies for the lateness of my reply.&#13;
&#13;
This solution was developed for an eZ Publish 3.8 site (with 3.9 compatibility in mind) several years ago. The customer was very happy and has yet to request an update or upgrade.&#13;
&#13;
You are correct in your assumption that the eZ Publish default kernel module, 'shop' is required / expected in the correct function of this solution.&#13;
&#13;
The shop module is available in all copies of eZ Publish by default (it may not be enabled but we are certain you have a copy).&#13;
&#13;
You would not have had to install the shop module while performing the initial installation of eZ Publish. This is included and provided by default. It would actually be more difficult to remove it and would not be omitted under any normal circumstances.&#13;
&#13;
Thank you for your positive feedback! It is very good to know that other people with newer versions of eZ Publish are making use of this solution.&#13;
&#13;
Please feel free to write a positive review :)&#13;
&#13;
Cheers,&#13;
Heath</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (// Heath)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/bcsimplesubscription/forum/general/shop_module_required/re_shop_module_required</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 19 Jul 2009 16:36:42 +0000</pubDate>
